--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This package has the folowing content:
* this directory:
** README       - this file
** LICENSE.CC-BY-NC-ND-4.0 file with the text of the CC-BY-NC-ND-4.0 license
** all required Python scripts and executables
* MLatomF_src   - directory with the Fortran and C++ source code
* documentation - a directory with brief instructions on installation of the third-party packages
* example       - a directory containing example files including:
** mlatom.inp   - example of input file for delta-learning
** mlatom.saved - example of output file
** test.sh      - example of a command to run MLatom calculations using mlatom.inp input file and compare the result with mlatom.saved (if calculations are successful, it ends without any message). You can compare mlatom.out with mlatom.saved to make sure that calculations finished successfully.

